@realmoney Blind To Breadth? I am hearing a lot of euphoria in the financial media based on this week's market advance. To some, it is confirmation that a new Bull Market leg lies ahead. But, no one (I mean no one!) has even observed that the +250 point rise in the DJIA and

the 16 point climb in the S&P has been delivered while the market's breadth is exactly flat (with 1460 advancers and 1475 decliners on the NYSE). @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @lizclaman @Sarge986 @riskreversal

@realmoney I Am Bearish on Bonds Treasuries are getting smoked today. $TLT is -$3.40/share as the ten year US note yield is +16 basis points (to 1.97%). I dont recall of this magnitude in years. I remain of the view that the bond market made a generational low in yields back
in June, 2016. And, I remain short bonds - and expect to be short bonds for the next several years. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @riskreversal @Sarge986 @lizclaman

@realmoney Paring Down my Bank Stock Holdings Now * Reluctantly and given the strong price performance of the last few months With the move this week and given the strong follow through today (producing high relative strength readings), I am reluctantly reducing my very large

holdings in $GS, $C, $WFC and $BAC to medium sized now. All three stocks are now within ten percent of my year end 2020 price targets - making the upside reward v downside risk substantially less attractive than existed a few months ago. I will book some very good gains.
